  <h2 class="sec-title" id="weatherTitle">When to Visit <em>Nagaland</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="weatherNote" style="margin-bottom:0">Nagaland has three seasons: cool winter (October–February), warm spring (March–May) and monsoon (June–September). October to April is ideal — the Hornbill Festival is in early December, Dzükou Valley wildflowers bloom in June-July (accessible from October) and winter brings clear mountain views. March-May is excellent for rhododendrons and bird migration.</p>
